'''''The New Jedi Order: Recovery''''' is the first [[eBook]] and seventh installment of [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''The New Jedi Order'']] series set in the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]. This [[Wikipedia:short story|short story]] by [[Troy Denning]] sets the stage for much of the novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]'' and shows a slow reconciliation between [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and his wife [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]]. It is included as prologue in the paperback version of ''Star by Star''.

==Publisher's summary==
''As the forces of darkness threaten to engulf the galaxy, one last defiant spark remains&hellip;. Though the Yuuzhan Vong were victorious in their savage conquest of the planet Duro, they failed to extract sensitive information from Leia Organa Solo, who now barely clings to life after enduring the enemies' torture. Unless she receives medical attention soon, the badly wounded Princess and former head of the New Republic will surely die. Pursued by bounty hunters, Han Solo begins a race against time, only to find his urgent pleas for help rejected by planet after planet, as the Jedi are blamed for the continuing fight against the seemingly invincible aliens. Desperate, the Solos decide on a suicide mission. They must reach Coruscant, the New Republic's strife-ridden capital where traitors, appeasers, and assassins now share the same goal as the fierce Yuuzhan Vong: kill all Jedi&hellip;.

==Plot summary==
After being [[Torture/Legends|tortured]] by the hands of [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] is in need of immediate medical attention. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] rushes her to [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]], where they enter a [[Medcenter/Legends|medcenter]] under assumed names and she is tended by a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]-sympathetic [[Doctor/Legends|doctor]]. After Tsavong Lah's ultimatum to [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] – turn over the Jedi in exchange for a cease in the terrible [[Yuuzhan Vong]] hostilities – [[Peace Brigade]] thugs infiltrate the medcenter to attack Leia. Han fends them off with the help of [[Eelysa]], another Jedi there for medical treatment.

Leia and Han worm their way past Han's opportunistic cousin, [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]], who has ridden a tide of popularity for his role in defending Corellia, and now leads the [[Centerpoint Party]], a [[Politics/Legends|political]] entity that has no qualms over striking deals with the Yuuzhan Vong. Han, Leia and Eelysa depart Corellia aboard the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|Millennium Falcon]], aided by the [[Wild Knights]], a Jedi [[Starfighter/Legends|fighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] led by Eelysa's apprentice, [[Saba Sebatyne]]. As Leia continues her recuperation at the Wild Knight's secret headquarters at [[Cinnabar Moon]], she also mends her strained relationship with Han. The two piece together evidence from the [[Duros/Legends|Duro]] debacle and realize [[Viqi Shesh]] is collaborating with the Yuuzhan Vong.

Han and Leia return to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] to accuse the [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] as Shesh leads a movement in the Senate to officially appease the Yuuzhan. Shesh's vote fails, and Han and Leia are unable to make their evidence stick to the ultimately [[Death/Legends|death]] of Shesh's [[Chief of Staff/Legends|chief of staff]]. His ersatz deathbed confession absolves Shesh of all guilt and allows her to stay in power. The Jedi are left with few friends in the galaxy, but [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] begins planning an underground network of safe passage for the beleaguered [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]], which he dubs “the [[Great River]].”

